        # If any part of the OR sequence is true, the whole expression is true

def my_func(input1: str) -> bool:
    def eval_and(expr):
        # Evaluate all AND operations ('t&f' -> 'f')
        parts = expr.split('&')
        result = 't' if all(part == 't' for part in parts) else 'f'
        return result

    def eval_expression(expr):
        # Evaluate the expression by handling AND operations first
        # Split by OR operator and evaluate each sub-expression connected by AND
        parts = expr.split('|')
        results = [eval_and(part) for part in parts]
        # Return true if any of the OR-connected sub-expressions is true
        return any(result == 't' for result in results)

    # Return the result of the evaluated expression
    return eval_expression(input1)

def my_func(expression: str) -> bool:
    # Define a helper function to evaluate a simple expression
    def eval_simple_expr(expr):
        # Split the expression by '&' to handle AND operations first
        and_parts = expr.split('&')
        # Evaluate each part as True (t) or False (f)
        result = all(part == 't' for part in and_parts)
        return result

    # Split the expression by '|' to handle OR operations
    or_parts = expression.split('|')
    # Evaluate each part using the helper function
    result = any(eval_simple_expr(part) for part in or_parts)
    return result
